elements.name: processingDistrictPortCode
elements.description: The code for the U.S. port where the enclosed transaction(s) are to be ‘processed’.

elements.name: filerCode
elements.description: Filer’s identification code (as assigned by CBP).

elements.name: processingFilerOfficeCode
elements.description: A code agreed upon by the Filer and CBP representing a specific Filer ‘office’ (or sub-location).

elements.name: applicationIdentifierCode
elements.description: A code that identifies the type of transaction data within the block.

elements.name: filerPreparersUserDataText
elements.description:
Provided for the Filer/Preparer’s internal use. These positions are returned, unmodified, in the B-Record returned in the response to the block.
Space fill if not used.

elements.name: remotePreparerPort
elements.description:
For a B-Record returned in response to an input: the code for the U.S. port location of the Remote Preparer.
For ACE generated notifications: always space fill.

elements.name: remotePreparerFilerCode
elements.description:
For a B-Record returned in response to an input: Remote Filer’s (Preparer) identification code (as assigned by CBP).
For ACE generated notifications: always space fill.

elements.name: remotePreparerOfficeCode
elements.description:
For a B-Record returned in response to an input: a code agreed upon by the Remote Preparer and CBP representing a specific Preparer ‘office’ (or sub-location).
For ACE generated notifications: always space fill.

elements.name: remotelyFieldIndicator
elements.description:
For a B-Record returned in response to an input: an indication that the block has been prepared and filed remotely in accordance with the Broker District permit rules as set forth in CBP regulation.
1 = Remote Entry submission.
For ACE generated notifications: always space fill.

elements.name: filerPreparersUserDataText
elements.description: For a B-Record returned in response to an input: the exact value submitted in the input B-Record.
